Congress, Social Security Amendments of 1954 (H.R. 9366)
The Social Security Amendments of 1954 were signed into law on September 1, 1954, by President Eisenhower.
In his February 2, 1953, State of the Union Mes sage, President Eisenhower recommended that the "old age and survivors insurance should promptly be expanded to cover millions of citizens who have been left out
U.S. Congress.
Conference Committee, 1952.
Social Security Act of 1952.
