I think that requires a little discussion and a little understanding.
We all agree that on an ordinary tax bill it is not feasible or practi cal to write it on the floor of the House, and therefore we have adopted the theory that we have closed rules on tax bills.
But all we asked for in the Rules Committee was that the individual members of this House be given an opportunity to offer amendments to designate what classifications of persons should be includ 98-D, 1-I) ed."
On June 1, 1954, by a vote of 270 to 76(5-R, 71-D), debate of the closed rule was cut off, and the closed then adopted by voice vote. b.
