Mr. motion was rejected by voice vote.
/ b.
On August 17, 1967, the House passed 12080 by a roll call vote of 416 (182-R, 234-D) to 3 (l-R, 2-D).
The bill was debated under a closed rule prohibiting floor amendments.
Most of the debate centered on the new welfare
