Senate Action
The Senate Finance Committee held hearings on H.R. 12080 in August and September.
On November 14, 1967, it reported a heavily amended bill that
contained several of the OASDI provisions as they had been recommended by the Administration rather than as they had been modified by the House.
The Senate bill provided a 15 percent across-the-board social security increase, in con trast to the 12.5 percent increase in the House bill, and contained AFDC work training provisions passed by the House, but in a modified version that exempted mothers of preschool children.
