Adoption of the report came over the vigorous objections who were opposed to the welfare provisions: mandatory work regis tration for "appropriate" member6 of AFDC families whose father was neither dead nor disabled, but continuously absent from home, and the freeze in the proportion of a State's AFDC children who could receive Federal matching funds.
