CRS-63 P. 91-172, The Tax Reform Act of 1969 (H.R. 13270) The Tax Reform Act of 1969 was signed by President Nixon on December 30, 1969.
The President said that the decision to sign had not been easy.
The new
law included a 15 percent increase in social security benefits beginning in January 1, 1970.
1.
House Action 13270 by a vote of 395 to 30.
