CRS-67 R. P.L. 92-336, Public Debt Limit; Disaster Losses; Social Security Act, Amendments (H.R. 15390) 15390 was signed into law on July 1, 1972, by President Nixon.
At the beginning of the year, a number of changes in the social security system were proposed, along with the President's controversial welfare reform plan, in H.R. 1.
arate Congress at mid-year used a more promising vehicle to pass a sep The increase was added
