The bill remained in the Senate for more than a year because of contro The Senate finally approved H.R. 1 with a provision
versy over welfare reform.
for tests of rival welfare plans, but in conference all family welfare provi sions were dropped.
In addition, the final version of H.R. 1 contained provi
sions federalizing and consolidating adult public assistance programs for needy aged, blind, and disabled persons in a new "Supplemental Security Income" program.
