(Hereafter cited as Social Security Amendments of 1977: Legislative History) 9346 was introduced it was referred solely to the Ways and The Chairman of the Post Office and Civil Service Committee, Mr. Nix (D-Pa.), concerned over the social security coverage of Federal employ ees under the bill, successfully persuaded the Speaker of the House to give his Committee sequential referral of the bill.
The Committee on Post Office and Civil Service unanimously voted to amend the bill to strike social security coverage of Federal employees.
