/ On October 26, 1977, Mr. Pickle (D-Tex.) offered an amendment to strike another Committee provision authorizing standby loans to the OASDI system from general revenues whenever trust fund re- serves dipped below 25 percent of a year's outgo.
Mr. Pickle argued that any use of general treasury funds for social security undermined the contributory nature of the program.
He remarked that he did not want to see the Social Security program turned into a **welfare or need program."
