On October 26, 1977, Mr. (D-Calif.) offered an amendment to eliminate the minimum social security benefit for new benefi ciaries.
Mr. asserted that the minimum benefit guaranteed a beneficiary with very low social security contributions a monthly cash benefit "far in excess of his or her average monthly wage."
He further remarked that his amendment restored mea sure of the social insurance principle of relating benefits to contributions."
The amendment was rejected by a vote of 131 (68-R, 63-D) to 271 (64-R, 207-D).
