Senate Action
Preliminary hearings and mark-up sessions on financing and decoupling were held by the Senate Committee on Finance in the summer and fall of 1977, even though the House had not yet passed its social security bill.
/
Before H.R. 9346 was passed by the House, the Finance Committee had tenta tively agreed that its amendments would be attached to H.R. 5322, an unrelated tariff bill that had originated in the House.
H.R. 5322 was to be a convenient
vehicle for putting the Senate Finance Committee proposals before the Senate promptly.
