Before enactment of the Social Security Amendments of 1977, used to determine social security benefit If a
two retirement (earnings) tests size and eligibility.
One was an annual test, the other a monthly test.
beneficiary earned more than the annual limit, his benefits were reduced $1 for every $2 of excess earnings until all social security benefits were phased out.
Under the monthly earnings test, however, if a person's earnings were less than one-twelfth of the annual amount, he could get full benefits for that month, regardless of annual earnings.
