CRS-96 The adoption of the rule for floor consideration of the reconciliation bill became, in itself, a highly controversial issue.
The Democratic leader- ship argued for allowing six separate votes on the grounds that this would allow for greater accountability for individual Members and avoid criticisms of "rubber-stamping" the Administration's proposals.
