P.L. 98-460, Social Security Disability Benefits Reform Act of 1984 3755) / The Social Security Disability Benefits Reform Act of 1984 was signed into law on October 9, 1984, by President Reagan.
98-460 ended more than three
years of controversy over the Administration's efforts to rid the Disability Insurance program of ineligible recipients through an expanded periodic review process that had commenced in March 1981.
rized by the 1980 disability amendments.
The expanded reviews had been autho /
